article.headline: James Madison 45, Coastal Carolina 10
article.story: HARRISONBURG, Va. (AP) -- Scott Noble ran for two touchdowns and Jamal Sullivan ran for two more to lead James Madison to a 45-10 win over Coastal Carolina on Saturday. James Madison (3-1) never trailed, taking the lead less than five minutes into the game as L.C. Baker scored on a 35-yard pass from Rodney Landers. The Dukes led 28-0 at the half. Landers threw for 163 yards and one touchdown and ran for 129 yards and another score. Noble rushed for 55 yards on 9 carries, including scoring runs of 11 and one. Sullivan gained 28 yards on seven carries, with scoring runs of five and four. William Richardson went 15-for-25 and threw for 109 yards and one touchdown for the Chanticleers (1-3). Jerome Simpson caught four passes for 39 yards, including a six-yard touchdown. James Madison ran 232 yards to Coastal Carolina's 47.
